    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>white long grain rice</strong> to a pot with a lid with 225ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[300ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[450ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 12-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p><p>Once done, remove from the heat and set aside (lid on) to steam until serving</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-chilli-beef-with-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the rice is cooking, peel and grate your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Peel and cut your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong> into quarters, then separate the wedges so you end up with a pile of onion petals</p><p>Deseed your <strong>pepper[s]</strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-chilli-beef-with-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>diced beef</strong> to a bowl with the <strong>grated garlic</strong>, <strong>half </strong>your <strong>soy sauce</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p><p>Tip: Unevenly sized diced beef? Chop any larger pieces into smaller ones!</p><p>Add your <strong>cornflour </strong>and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> to the <strong>marinated beef</strong> and give everything a good mix up until the beef is fully coated \u2013 this is your <strong>coated beef</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-chilli-beef-with-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a very generous drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> (enough to cover the whole base of the pan) over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>coated beef</strong> to the pan and cook for 3-4 min on each side or until golden and crisp</p><p>Once crisp, transfer to a plate and set aside \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy beef</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-chilli-beef-with-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the beef is cooking, heat a separate large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>onion petals </strong>and <strong>pepper strips </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until beginning to soften</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-chilli-beef-with-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, combine your <strong>red chilli relish</strong>, <strong>tomato ketchup</strong>, <strong>rice vinegar</strong>, <strong>remaining soy sauce</strong> and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> in a bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>chilli sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-chilli-beef-with-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the vegetables have softened, add the <strong>crispy beef</strong> and <strong>chilli sauce</strong> to the pan and stir it all together</p><p>Cook for a further 2-3 min or until the sauce has thickened and the beef is cooked through (no pink meat!) \u2013 this is your <strong>crispy chilli beef</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/crispy-chilli-beef-with-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>crispy chilli beef </strong>over the <strong>cooked rice</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
